{"questionId":"9084400","questionHtml":"<p>Two containers, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math>, are filled with an ideal gas at the same pressure.</p>\n<p>The volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math> is four times the volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math>. The temperature of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math> is 327 °C and the temperature&nbsp;of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math> is 27 °C.</p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>amount</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>substance</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>in</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>amount</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>substance</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>in</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> ?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084400","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.HL.TZ0.17","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Two containers, X and Y, are filled with an ideal gas at the same pressure. The volume of X is four times the volume of Y. The temperature of X is 327 °C and the temperature of Y i","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNum